{"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse\/InverseTheme"],"anchor":"Group","title":"Group"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This is an override of the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudsthemesorange\/","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" with some inverted colors. It can override any properties from its superclass. We did not plan to make ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse\/InverseTheme","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" derivable."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The aim of the theme is to provide a particular set of colors for dedicated applications and use cases, like for example B2B apps or teams needing eye comfort. It can be seen as an extended dark mode."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"How to use the theme","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"How-to-use-the-theme"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse\/InverseTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" directly. You will have to use the "},{"code":"OUDSThemeableView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for your root view and give it an instance of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse\/InverseTheme","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". Keep in mind the themes are "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift class objects"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and can be heavy, so you may use only as instance as singleton and not store any properties."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["import OUDS \/\/ To get OUDSThemeableView","import OUDSThemeInverse \/\/ To get Inverseheme","import SwiftUI","","@main","struct YourApp: App {","    var body: some Scene {","        WindowGroup {","            OUDSThemeableView(theme: InverseTheme()) {","                \/\/ Your root view","            }","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Then, in your views, you can simply use the theme through an environment variable to get the tokens:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import OUDS \/\/ To get the theme environment variable","import SwiftUI","","struct SomeView: View {","","    \/\/ Get OUDS environment variable for theme thanks to themeable view","    @Environment(\\.theme) var theme","    ","    var body: some View {","        ","        \/\/ Use the theme to retrieve the tokens","        \/\/ For spaces: theme.spaces","        \/\/ For sizes: theme.sizes","        \/\/ For borders: theme.borders","        \/\/ For elevations: theme.elevations","        \/\/ For opacities: theme.opacities","        \/\/ For colors: theme.colors","    }","}",""]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"OUDSThemesInverse"}],"role":"collection","symbolKind":"module","roleHeading":"Framework","title":"OUDSThemesInverse","externalID":"OUDSThemesInverse"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"text":"This theme overrides the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Orange theme"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" for some colors so as to bring an “inverse”-colored experience."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudsthemesinverse"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse"},"references":{"doc://ouds-ios.OUDSThemesInverse/documentation/OUDSThemesInverse":{"title":"OUDSThemesInverse","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/oudsthemesinverse","abstract":[{"text":"This theme overrides the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Orange theme","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" for some colors so as to bring an “inverse”-colored experience.","type":"text"}]},"https://ios.unified-design-system.orange.com/documentation/oudsthemesorange/":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudsthemesorange\/","title":"Orange theme","url":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudsthemesorange\/","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Orange theme"}]},"doc://ouds-ios.OUDSThemesInverse/documentation/OUDSThemesInverse/InverseTheme":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse\/InverseTheme","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This is an override of the default basic "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OrangeTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" with some inverted colors."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It can overrides any properties from its superclass, but is not derivable."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"InverseTheme","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/oudsthemesinverse\/inversetheme","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"InverseTheme"}],"title":"InverseTheme","type":"topic","kind":"symbol"}}}